I believe that the Mark deficit should *NOT* be repudiated, and so to
make up some of the difference, I proto the following:

Proto-PROPOSAL DB7  (Vanyel)
Nomic Taxes
(Creates a Rule)

Exactly once every Nomic Week, the Banker shall deduct .05 Mark from the
Account of every Player who has more than 1 Mark.  These deducted Marks
shall be added to the Bank.  

***END PROTO

This will provide a method (albeit slow) of returning Marks to the Bank.
The .05 Mark seemed sufficiently low... although that can be modified.
The 1 Mark minimum is there to prevent players "living in abject poverty"
from having to pay taxes.

At any rate, we need some way of returning Marks to the Bank without
repudiating the debt.  I also thought, perhaps, that a percentage tax
might work, but that would be up to you guys. (gals, its, etc.)

Vanyel


