"Don" == Don Blaheta <blahedo@quincy.edu> writes:

Don> Exactly once every Nomic Week, the Banker shall deduct .05 Mark
Don> from the Account of every Player who has more than 1 Mark.  These
Don> deducted Marks shall be added to the Bank.

eek!  a tax!  and not only that, but a regressive tax!

i'd rather see a 1% per week tax than a flat tax.  this would be a way
of dealing with mark inflation, however.  if you want to give poverty
protection, make it 1% per week, with the first mark exempt _for
players only_.  groups get no tax break.  groups should definitely
have to pay any tax that players have to pay; else everyone will
transfer all their marks into their group treasuries.

we also need to stop destroying marks when players leave the game.  i
would rather see these transferred to the Bank.

k.
--
kelly martin                                 <kelly@poverty.bloomington.in.us>
