"Don" == Don Blaheta <blahedo@quincy.edu> writes:

Don> Exactly once every Nomic Week, the Banker shall deduct 1% from
Don> the Mark Accounts of all Players and Groups, and any other
Don> Mark-Possessing Entities except the Bank.  Players who have 1
Don> Mark or less are exempt from this requirement.  All proceeds from
Don> this Tax shall be added to the Bank.

this is reasonably close to what i'd like, although i would write it
as

      At noon GMT on Monday of each Nomic Week, a tax of 1% of all
      Marks held by Players in excess of 1.00 Mark, and of 1% of all
      Marks held by all non-Player Entities excluding the Bank, shall
      be levied.  This tax shall be collected by the Banker, and all
      revenues resulting from this tax shall be deposited in the Bank.

1% per week results in a 50% depletion in 69 weeks -- in other words,
after 69 weeks the Bank will have collected 50% of the Marks held by
Players as taxes (the actual value is close to 68.9675639).  each
doubling of the percentage halves this depletion time.  a 5% rate will
make the 50% depletion time roughly 13.5 weeks, or just about three
months.

i haven't received any of the Banker's records yet so i can't say how
many Marks there are out there, as well as the total quantity of Marks
held in arrears.  as soon as i know these data it will be easier for
me to recommend a tax rate.

k.
--
kelly martin                                 <kelly@poverty.bloomington.in.us>
