> ***END PROTO
> 

One point I would make is that the tax should be on only the portion
of accounts over 1 Mark.  This reflects the way income taxes work in
the UK and (I presume) most other countries.  In this case, it
hardly matters, but on general principles it should be this way so
as not to discourage wealth creation.  In our taxation system, for
example, incomes up to about UK#5000 are untaxed, the next #25000 or
so are taxed at 25%, and those over #30000 are taxed at 40%.  If the 
system worked like DB7, when someone's salary increased from 29000
to 30000, their net income would go from 21750 to 18000.  But only
the part actually over #30000 is taxed at 40%, so your net income
never goes down when your gross goes up.

If we are ever going to expand the taxation system, this might
become important, so we should set the right precedent now.

	Blue


