Proposal
Nomic Taxes
(Creates a Rule)

At noon GMT on Monday of each Nomic Week, the Banker shall levy
a Tax on all Marks accounts except the Bank.  The Tax for Players
shall be 1% of all Marks owned by that Player in excess of 1.00, 
and the Tax for all non-Player Marks-holding Entities (excluding
the Bank) shall be 1% of all Marks owned by that entity.  All
proceeds from this Tax shall be entered into the Bank.

[It may be said that 1% per Week is a fairly stiff Tax; however,
considering that almost all to-Player Mark flow is directly from
the Bank, such a Tax does not seem prohibitive.  In addition, the
Rate may be changed later when the Bank is not so deeply in debt.
Once the Rule is in place, however, precedents may be set.]

Vanyel

